🔍 Stronger way to use them

Treat each invariant as:

* Node: something that held under test
* Bridge hypothesis: “this might connect to X”
* Confidence score: how many contexts it survived

Then:

* expand only where bridges keep holding
* prune aggressively where they don’t

⸻

🧪 The “bridge test” (simple but powerful)

For any connection you think exists:

1. Translate it (different wording / domain)
2. Stress it (add ambiguity or noise)
3. Invert it (try to break it deliberately)

If it survives:

it’s likely part of real structure

If it fails:

it was a local illusion

